election_record.label: Pennsylvania 1789 Electoral College

overview.note: The Documentary History of the First Federal Elections lists 6306 votes for John Arndt, 6296 votes for James Wilson, 5951 votes for Alexander Graydon and 423 votes for David Rittenhouse.

sub_unit.name: Newtown
sub_unit.note: The total from Newtown district is reported as 333 votes per candidate but the township totals add up to 331 each.

sub_unit.name: Two
sub_unit.note: The Second District of Cumberland County includes Rye, Tyrone, and Teboyn townships.

sub_unit.name: Shippenburgh
sub_unit.note: The Shippenburgh District of Cumberland County includes Hopewell, Newton, and Shippenburgh townships.

sub_unit.name: Fayette
sub_unit.note: "Not enough people appeared on election day to hold an election [in Fayette County]." The Documentary History of the First Federal Elections. Edited by Merrill Jensen and Robert A. Becker. 389.

sub_unit.name: Franklin
sub_unit.note: Alexander Graydon received 3 votes as Alexander Grayson.

sub_unit.name: Philadelphia
sub_unit.note: The Democratic-Republicans of Philadelphia: The Origins, 1776-1797 and The Documentary History of the First Federal Elections list 1530 votes for James Wilson.

sub_unit.name: North
sub_unit.note: James Wilson received 1 vote as John Wilson.

sub_unit.name: Westmoreland
sub_unit.note: David Rittenhouse received 1 vote as Daniel Rittenhouset.

sub_unit.name: York
sub_unit.note: John Arndt received 1 vote as Jonathan Arndt.
